      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "I'm really sorry you're feeling this way, and I want to tell you that your feelings are valid, but they don't define your worth as a parent. Every parent struggles with tough days, and it's okay to feel overwhelmed or like you've made mistakes. What matters most is how you respond to those feelings and how you move forward.\n\nYou mentioned your kids deserve better, but the fact that you're reflecting on your actions and caring about their well-being shows that you love them deeply. That love is already doing more for them than you might realize. Instead of focusing on what went wrong, try to focus on what you can do today to support them and yourself.\n\nWould you like to talk about what happened today so we can unpack it together? Or maybe you'd like some gentle strategies to help you feel more grounded and hopeful? I'm here to listen without judgment.",
